narratives.question_text: What were your expectations for this studio and how well were they met?
Were the resources available to you - library, fabrication labs, classroom, software, desk space, etc. - adequate for the fulfillment of the assigned work?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: The resources were adequate although specific information on CHandigarh was at times difficult to find (although I am not sure anything can be done about this)

narratives.question_text: Comment on the most and least valuable aspects of the studio
comments: The discussions that the studio fostered (informally and during pin-ups) were the most valuable aspect of the experience. We had a great group of intelligent, motivated students who all participated in the studio in different, equally meaningful ways.
I think desk-crits or pin-ups every Monday and Thursday are too much and doesn't leave enough room for the students.

All peripheral aspects to this studio, namely lectures, involvement of forestry faculty, and various last minute outside critics was next to useless. Actually I feel it was severely detrimental to the studio and a large waste of time. This was a great premise for a studio that through over complications, too many people involved, and lack of a cohesive vision unfortunately fell pretty flat.
